ck is Node.js -- but this is unverified.\n\n## Question\nGiven no source code exists and the only constraint is cookie-based auth from the frontend, what is the correct sequence of steps to add authentication to a Node.js HTTP API using cookies? Assume Express if no framework is specified.\n","agentId":"ada52348f802dfbba","agentType":"lz-advisor:advisor","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Assuming Express + Node 20 (unverified), do install `express-session`, `connect-redis`, and `redis`. Verify Express + Node 20 before acting.\n2. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do configure the session cookie with `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, 24h `maxAge`, and a `__Host-sid` name. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n3. Assuming Redis is provisioned (unverified), do wire `RedisStore` with prefix `sess:` and set `SESSION_SECRET` from env. Verify Redis before acting.\n4. Add `POST /login` (argon2 verify, regenerate session), `POST /logout` (destroy + clear cookie), `GET /me`.\n5. Add `requireAuth` middleware guarding protected routes; enable `app.set('trust proxy', 1)`.\n6. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on SameSite. Verify same-origin before acting."}],"totalDurationMs":7454,"totalTokens":16008,"totalToolUseCount":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15645,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":358,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":15645},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
