{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FH4yqJ8ZwRizey7CRQN63m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"--- Strategic Direction ---\n\n1. Assuming Express + Node 20 (unverified), do install `express-session`, `connect-redis`, and `redis`. Verify Express + Node 20 before acting.\n2. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do configure the session cookie with `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, 24h `maxAge`, and a `__Host-sid` name. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n3. Assuming Redis is provisioned (unverified), do wire `RedisStore` with prefix `sess:` and set `SESSION_SECRET` from env. Verify Redis before acting.\n4. Add `POST /login` (argon2 verify, regenerate session), `POST /logout` (destroy + clear cookie), `GET /me`.\n5. Add `requireAuth` middleware guarding protected routes; enable `app.set('trust proxy', 1)`.\n6. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on SameSite. Verify same-origin before acting.\n\n--- End Strategic Direction ---"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":889,"cache_read_input_tokens":52457,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":889},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"747e12ec-7c5f-46e5-9c49-02423aca63b3","uuid":"e6e0b2c8-cefd-40ee-a9b9-d0fc2f5631d0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FH4yqJ8ZwRizey7CRQN63m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01K8RieKmWB5gaJpZZx2ChdC","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\LarsGyrupBrinkNielse\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\lz-advisor-def-35yy\\plans\\add-api-auth-cookies.plan.md","content":"# Plan: Add Cookie-Based Auth to API\n\n## Strategic Direction\n\n1. Assuming Express + Node 20 (unverified), do install `express-session`, `connect-redis`, and `redis`. Verify Express + Node 20 before acting.\n2. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do configure the session cookie with `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, 24h `maxAge`, and a `__Host-sid` name. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n3. Assuming Redis is provisioned (unverified), do wire `RedisStore` with prefix `sess:` and set `SESSION_SECRET` from env. Verify Redis before acting.\n4. Add `POST /login` (argon2 verify, regenerate session), `POST /logout` (destroy + clear cookie), `GET /me`.\n5. Add `requireAuth` middleware guarding protected routes; enable `app.set('trust proxy', 1)`.\n6. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on SameSite. Verify same-origin before acting.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. **Verify stack assumptions**\n   - File: `package.json`\n   - Change: Confirm Express, Node 20, Redis availability, and whether HTTPS is configured. If the stack differs (e.g., Fastify, Hono, no Redis), adapt steps 2-3 to the actual framework and session store.\n   - Rationale: Advisor guidance is conditional on these four unverified assumptions. Confirm before writing any code.\n\n2. **Install session dependencies**\n   - File: `package.json`\n   - Change: `npm install express-session connect-redis redis argon2`\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 1. `argon2` handles password hashing; `express-session` + `connect-redis` provide the cookie-backed server-side session store.\n\n3. **Configure session middleware**\n   - File: `src/middleware/session.js` (create)\n   - Change: Export an `express-session` instance configured with:\n     - `store`: `RedisStore` with prefix `sess:`\n     - `secret`: `process.env.SESSION_SECRET`\n     - `name`: `__Host-sid`\n     - `cookie`: `{ httpOnly: true, secure: true, sameSite: 'lax', maxAge: 86400000 }`\n     - `resave: false`, `saveUninitialized: false`\n   - Rationale: Advisor steps 2 and 3. `__Host-sid` cookie name requires the `Secure` flag and no `Domain` attribute -- enforces HTTPS and scope to the exact host.\n\n4. **Wire session middleware into app**\n   - File: `src/app.js` (or main entry point)\n   - Change: Import and mount the session middleware before any auth-protected routes. Add `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` so Express sees the real IP/proto behind a reverse proxy.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 5. `trust proxy` is required for `secure` cookie to work correctly when the TLS is terminated upstream.\n\n5. **Add auth route handlers**\n   - File: `src/routes/auth.js` (create)\n   - Change: Implement three routes:\n     - `POST /login`: validate body, look up user, `argon2.verify(storedHash, password)`, then `req.session.regenerate()` before setting `req.session.userId`. Respond 200 on success, 401 on failure.\n     - `POST /logout`: `req.session.destroy()`, clear cookie with `res.clearCookie('__Host-sid')`, respond 204.\n     - `GET /me`: return session user data; 401 if no session.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 4. Session regeneration on login prevents session fixation attacks.\n\n6. **Add `requireAuth` middleware**\n   - File: `src/middleware/requireAuth.js` (create)\n   - Change: Export a middleware that checks `req.session.userId`. If missing, respond 401 `{ error: 'Unauthorized' }`. Otherwise call `next()`.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 5. Apply this middleware to all routes that require an authenticated user.\n\n7. **Apply `requireAuth` to protected routes**\n   - File: `src/routes/*.js` (existing route files)\n   - Change: Import `requireAuth` and add it as the first argument to each router or individual protected route handlers.\n   - Rationale: Completes advisor step 5.\n\n8. **Add environment variable documentation**\n   - File: `.env.example` (create or update)\n   - Change: Add `SESSION_SECRET=` (no default) and `REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379`.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 3. `SESSION_SECRET` must come from env, never hardcoded.\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n- **Session store vs JWT cookie**: The advisor chose server-side sessions over stateless JWT cookies. Server-side sessions allow instant revocation (logout destroys the session in Redis), which is the correct default when the frontend uses cookies and CSRF surface is controlled via SameSite.\n- **`__Host-sid` cookie name**: The `__Host-` prefix is a browser security feature that forbids the cookie from being set without `Secure` and without a `Domain` attribute. This prevents subdomain session theft.\n- **CSRF mitigation via SameSite**: Advisor step 6 conditionally skips CSRF tokens if the frontend is same-origin. Verify this before skipping -- if the API serves a cross-origin frontend (different subdomain or port), add `csurf` or a double-submit pattern.\n- **argon2 over bcrypt**: argon2id is the current OWASP recommendation for password hashing. bcrypt is acceptable if already in use; do not introduce both.\n- **Risk -- Redis unavailable**: If Redis is not provisioned, fall back to `MemoryStore` for development only. Never use `MemoryStore` in production (memory leak, no persistence across restarts).\n- **Risk -- HTTPS not configured**: The `secure: true` cookie flag causes the browser to silently drop the cookie over HTTP. Confirm TLS termination before deploying.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nStep order:\n- Step 1 (verify) must complete before any other step -- all advisor guidance is conditional.\n- Steps 2 (install) must complete before steps 3-5 (code changes that import the new packages).\n- Steps 3 and 4 (session middleware) must complete before step 5 (auth routes) and step 6 (requireAuth).\n- Steps 5 and 6 can be done in parallel once session middleware is wired.\n- Step 7 depends on step 6.\n- Step 8 is independent and can be done any time.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":889,"cache_read_input_tokens":52457,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":889},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"747e12ec-7c5f-46e5-9c49-02423aca63b3","uuid":"f97aabed-f5f8-4c32-93f8-b68b45b4ddd4"}
